    "The data generated for the three case studies differ contextually depending on the relevant questions for each case study.",
    "Legal and ethical gapsAs stated earlier, the provisional AI Act proposes a strict liability regime for high-risk AI systems (Case Study 3).",
    "It means that for low-risk (Case Study 1) and mid-risk (Case Study 2) AI systems (limited risk under AI-Act), the AI-Act is partially applicable with voluntary compliance standards.Case Study 2 shows that the reasoning followed by the generated data is different for human experts, who are able to recognise the risk of a lawsuit from a neighbour.",
    "What do we learn from this consideration?",
    "Even though the AI recommended a proactive control without considering its consequences, a human expert may decide to follow the advice."
